# Disable suspect NIC offloads on Realtek 2.5GbE interfaces at
# link-up.
#
# Long-standing Realtek RTL8125 / RTL8125B / RTL8126 regression:
# the hardware claims TSO (TCP segmentation offload), GSO
# (generic segmentation offload), GRO (generic receive offload),
# and TX checksum offload, but in some firmware revisions emits
# malformed packets that peers (Debian apt mirrors, OCI
# registries, etc.) drop without telling the sender. Symptoms
# from the operator's perspective:
#
#   * DHCP succeeds (small packets, no offloads needed).
#   * ICMP succeeds (small packets).
#   * Any TCP transfer larger than a few packets stalls or
#     fails entirely. ``apt-get update`` errors with
#     ``Could not connect`` or ``Failed to fetch``. The live
#     env's ``pixie`` can't reach catalog.toml. Image fetches
#     hang mid-transfer.
#
# Disabling the offloads at the kernel-driver level forces the
# stack to do the segmentation + checksum in software. ~3-5%
# CPU cost on a sustained 2.5GbE transfer (which the mini-PCs
# this affects have plenty of headroom for) for "the link
# actually works".
#
# Fires for both ``r8125`` (out-of-tree DKMS) and ``r8169``
# (in-tree) because we can't always tell at bake time which
# driver the operator's appliance will end up with -- the modprobe
# alias prefers r8125 for RTL8125/RTL8126 device IDs, but a
# kernel update or operator override could put r8169 back in
# play. The udev rule fires on whichever driver bound the device.
#
# ``ATTR{type}=="1"`` filters to ethernet interfaces (skips
# tap / bridge / etc. that NetworkManager creates later).
#
# RUN+= runs as a one-shot when the device becomes ready. The
# offload state persists across NetworkManager link cycles -- the
# kernel keeps the disable setting until module unload.
ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="net", ATTR{type}=="1", DRIVERS=="r8125", \
    RUN+="/sbin/ethtool -K $env{INTERFACE} tso off gso off gro off lro off tx-checksum-ip-generic off"

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="net", ATTR{type}=="1", DRIVERS=="r8169", \
    RUN+="/sbin/ethtool -K $env{INTERFACE} tso off gso off gro off lro off tx-checksum-ip-generic off"
